# ULTRA Daily Improvement — HAP dashboards (340B + OW + print)

When working on **improvement tasks** (design polish, print view, accessibility, layout, text clarity, refactoring for novices), prefer the structured ULTRA workflow over ad-hoc requests. **Consider impact on all surfaces** (see **hap-multi-dashboard-scope** rule) when shared CSS or patterns change.

1. **Primary source:** [ULTRA-prompts.md](ULTRA-prompts.md) — v03–v07 (print, layout, accessibility), v08–v12 (50 improvements), **v13–v22 (100 novice refactor prompts)**.
2. **Refactoring manual:** [REFACTORING-CODEBASE-MANUAL.md](REFACTORING-CODEBASE-MANUAL.md) — daily refactor workflow, code map, labeling rules, reuse checklist.
3. **Workflow:** [DAILY-IMPROVEMENT.md](DAILY-IMPROVEMENT.md) — run next wave → update handoff → audit → commit. For novice refactor, run one prompt from v13–v22 per day.
4. **Rules/updates:** [AGENT-RULES-SYSTEM.md](AGENT-RULES-SYSTEM.md) — stability rules, release gate.

Use these prompts when the user asks for improvements, polish, "run ULTRA", or refactor for clarity so changes align with prior waves and handoff stays current.
